x4freetext: Figure 4.
The Calcium Target was a Natural Calcium Foil (99.6%
CA-40), Which was Rolled in Air to a Thickness of
5.8 Mg/Cm**2. As Calcium Oxidizes Very Rapidly When
Exposed to Air, the Target Prepared in this Way was
Heavily Contaminated with Oxygen, and in Fact was
Somewhat Wrinkled As a Results of Chemical Changes
Occurring After the Target was Mounted.

x4freetext: Figure 5.
The Calcium Target were Prepared by Evaporating
Natural Mettallic Calcium onto an Aluminium Backing
Under Vacuum.When the Calcium had Accumulated to
Convenient Thicknesses (MORE THAN 1 MG/CM**2) It Could
Easily be Peeled Off the Backing As a Smooth Foil and
Storage of the Target in Vacuum Immediately After
Mounting Considerably Reduced the Oxygen Contamination.
